Metorex Jumps to Two-Year High in Johannesburg After Saying It’s in Talks

-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 
2011-03-28T17:01:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/metorex-advances-to-a-28-month-high-after-saying-it-s-in-undisclosed-talks.html
Metorex Ltd. (MTX) , a producer of metals
and coal in  Africa , rose to the highest price in more than two
years in Johannesburg trading after saying it’s in talks that
could influence its share price.  Metorex advanced 3.6 percent to 6.32 rand as of 5 p.m.
local time, the highest close since Oct. 22, 2008, valuing the
company at 6.33 billion rand ($920 million).  “Metorex has entered into discussions which, if
successfully concluded, may have a material effect on the price
of the company’s securities,” the Johannesburg-based company
said today in a statement, without elaborating.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carli Lourens in Johannesburg at 
